activities.name: Informed Consent
activities.description: Obtain written informed consent from participant

activities.name: Serum Chemistry
activities.description: Serum chemistry laboratory assessment including ALT, AST, total bilirubin

activities.name: Pregnancy Test
activities.description: Pregnancy test for women of childbearing potential

activities.name: Hepatitis B/C and HIV Testing
activities.description: Serological tests for viral hepatitis A, B, C, E and HIV

activities.name: CT/MRI Scan
activities.description: Computed tomography or MRI scan for tumor assessment per RECIST 1.1

activities.name: Ramucirumab SC Administration
activities.description: Subcutaneous ramucirumab administration with loading dose and maintenance dose regimen

activities.name: Combination Therapy Administration
activities.description: Administration of combination therapy (paclitaxel, FOLFIRI, erlotinib, or docetaxel)

activities.name: PK Blood Sampling
activities.description: Pharmacokinetic blood sampling for ramucirumab concentration analysis

activities.name: Concomitant Medications
activities.description: Review and documentation of concomitant medications

notes.text: a. In Sub-Cohort B1, the loading dose will not be given
b. MD: Weekly dosing starting on Week 2 (Cycle 1 Day 8) except for B1 when it will be starting on Week 1 (Cycle 1, Day 1)
c. Only 1 dosing regimen (one LD - MD level) will be investigated in Sub-Cohort B2 and Sub-Cohort B3. Dose will be selected based on PK and safety data
LD = loading dose; MD = maintenance dose; QW = every week; SC = subcutaneous; Q2W = every 2 weeks
AUC = area under the plasma concentration versus time curve; eq = equivalent; F = bioavailability; IV = intravenous
